        return new MyService();
    }
}
ğŸ‘‰ So, in @SpringBootApplication, it tells Spring that this class can contain bean definitions.

2ï¸âƒ£ @EnableAutoConfiguration
This is the core feature of Spring Boot.

It tells Spring Boot to automatically configure your application based on the dependencies present in your classpath.

âœ… Example:

If you include spring-boot-starter-web, it auto-configures

Tomcat (embedded server)

DispatcherServlet

Spring MVC

JSON converters

ğŸ‘‰ You donâ€™t need to configure these manually!

If you include spring-boot-starter-data-jpa, it auto-configures:

