ğŸ§  How It Works (Execution Flow)
When you run:

SpringApplication.run(MyApp.class, args);
Spring Boot:

Creates an ApplicationContext

Scans for beans/components

Applies auto-configuration

Starts the embedded server (Tomcat/Jetty)

Runs your application ğŸš€

ğŸ§© Summary Table
Part	Role
@Configuration	Marks this class as a source of Spring bean definitions
@EnableAutoConfiguration	Automatically configures Spring beans based on classpath
@ComponentScan	Scans packages for Spring components
@SpringBootApplication	Combines all three to simplify configuration
âš™ï¸ Optional Attributes
Attribute	Description	Example
scanBasePackages	Packages to scan for components	@SpringBootApplication(scanBasePackages = "com.hotel")
exclude	Exclude specific auto-configurations	@SpringBootApplication(exclude = DataSourceAutoConfiguration.class)
ğŸŒŸ Example in Context
