    new Employee(1, "Akanksha", "IT", 60000),
    new Employee(2, "Riya", "HR", 55000),
    new Employee(3, "Raj", "IT", 75000),
    new Employee(4, "Rohit", "Finance", 50000),
    new Employee(5, "Riya", "HR", 55000) // duplicate
);
ğŸ¯ Common Stream Operations and Interview-Style Questions
Below are practical questions + examples you can practice.

ğŸ”¹ 1. Find All Unique Employees (Remove Duplicates)
List<Employee> unique = employees.stream()
        .distinct()
        .collect(Collectors.toList());
ğŸ‘‰ Make sure youâ€™ve overridden equals() and hashCode() (based on id).

ğŸ”¹ 2. Sort Employees by Salary (Ascending / Descending)
// Ascending
employees.stream()
        .sorted(Comparator.comparing(Employee::getSalary))
        .forEach(System.out::println);

// Descending
employees.stream()
        .sorted(Comparator.comparing(Employee::getSalary).reversed())
        .forEach(System.out::println);
ğŸ”¹ 3. Get Employees with Salary Greater Than 60000
employees.stream()
        .filter(e -> e.getSalary() > 60000)
        .forEach(System.out::println);
ğŸ”¹ 4. Find the Highest Paid Employee
Employee maxSalaryEmp = employees.stream()
        .max(Comparator.comparing(Employee::getSalary))
        .orElse(null);
System.out.println(maxSalaryEmp);
ğŸ”¹ 5. Find the Lowest Paid Employee
Employee minSalaryEmp = employees.stream()
        .min(Comparator.comparing(Employee::getSalary))
        .orElse(null);
System.out.println(minSalaryEmp);
ğŸ”¹ 6. Count Employees by Department
Map<String, Long> countByDept = employees.stream()
        .collect(Collectors.groupingBy(Employee::getDepartment, Collectors.counting()));
System.out.println(countByDept);
ğŸ§  Output Example:

{Finance=1, HR=2, IT=2}
ğŸ”¹ 7. Average Salary by Department
Map<String, Double> avgSalaryByDept = employees.stream()
        .collect(Collectors.groupingBy(Employee::getDepartment, Collectors.averagingDouble(Employee::getSalary)));
System.out.println(avgSalaryByDept);
ğŸ”¹ 8. Get List of Employee Names
List<String> names = employees.stream()
        .map(Employee::getName)
        .collect(Collectors.toList());
System.out.println(names);
ğŸ”¹ 9. Check if Any Employee Has Salary > 1,00,000
